Phew. That might have been the fastest we ever made a video. Literally working day and night. A huge challenge in talking about Corona was that the science is ongoing. So we put in extra special care to have good sources for this video and will update them in the coming weeks and months. Check them out here: https://sites.google.com/view/sourcescorona


We could not have made this video without experts who took time in one of the busiest periods of their own careers. A huge thanks especially to Dr James Gurney and Dr Max Roser of Our World in Data for helping us make sure the video was as accurate as it could be in a situation that is changing daily.


Also a big shoutout to https://ourworldindata.org/ – the online publication for research and data on the world’s largest problems – and how to make progress solving them. Check out their site. It also includes a constantly updated page on the Corona Pandemic. Working together with them over the years has been a delight.


Ok. We are very tired and are going to take a nap now. Stay healthy!

snippet.textDisplay:
Here's how you use critical thinking to break down a video like this.
At about 3:43, after all the scary description of the virus is over, is where the real "meat" is. Here are the claims:
-[The majority of people infected will get through it with relatively mild symptoms]
.....This is somewhat misleading, as it doesn't explicitly state that many people will never even know they had it (carriers). Maybe they say this later on, but placement of such statements is important due to how average public school-taught people think.
-[But many cases become severe or even critical, we don't know % because not all cases have been identified, but it's safe to say a lot more than with the flu]
.....It is not "safe to say" this. He literally just said we don't know how many ppl are infected, LET ALONE how many ppl are just unaffected carriers. Knowing these numbers is critical to knowing if it's "a lot more than the flu".
-[The next several scenes]
.....are just a description of severe flu cases. It's ridiculous.
-[It's much more dangerous, we know....it's much more contagious]
.....No they don't 😂 Show me the source on THAT one buddy! It doesn't even affect kids as dangerously as certain influenza strains, FACT.
-The rest is all predictive fear mongering.
You're welcome.

some of them said if you had come to these people who descended, perhaps some would have something with them, and they came to them and said: Oh, our master, if our

snippet.textDisplay: It's not true that the virus is spreading from China to the world. China is only the first country to discover new viruses, which does not mean that the virus was born in China. This only means that China can recognize new viruses more quickly, which shows the level of medical care in China. Most of the patients diagnosed in China are three generations of virus, and a small number of patients diagnosed are two generations of virus. However, the United States can find the first generation of virus and the second, third or fourth generation of confirmed patients, which shows that the virus has already spread in the United States, but the United States can not recognize the new virus. After two months in China, the number of confirmed cases has reached 80000, while in the United States, after only two weeks, the number of confirmed cases has reached 80000. As long as there is no diagnosis, there will be no definite diagnosis. There have been news reports before that some of the influenza outbreaks in the United States last year were actually infected with the virus, but doctors could not identify it, so they mistakenly classified it as influenza. Another point to make is to wear a mask when you go out. Whether you are sick or not, it is not only to protect yourself, but also to protect others.
